     2| * IVX Video Platform API — enterprise Instagram-grade video experience.
     3| *
     4| * Routes (registered in hono.ts under /api/ivx/video-platform/*):
     5| *   GET  /feed                        — CANONICAL unified feed (single source of truth for
     6| *                                       landing page, Android, iOS, Expo, desktop, TV).
     7| *                                       Deterministic identical order on every platform:
     8| *                                       3 investor deal videos → 1 featured investor video → repeat.
     9| *                                       Project reels (?type=reel) never interrupt the deal flow.
    10| *                                       (?channel=investor|buyer|realtor|builder|jv, ?type=reel,
    11| *                                        ?project_id=, ?viewer_id= (liked/saved flags only),
    12| *                                        ?zip=, ?cursor=, ?limit=)
    13| *   GET  /channels                    — audience channels + property channels with counts
    14| *   POST /events                      — analytics beacons (view/watch/complete/double_tap_like/share/profile)
    15| *   GET  /videos/:videoId/analytics   — per-video aggregates
    16| *   POST /videos/:videoId/meta        — tag audiences / property / zip / creator / story
    17| *   POST /videos/:videoId/report      — viewer report → moderation queue
    18| *   POST /follow                      — toggle follow { follower_id, creator_id }
    19| *   GET  /follow/:followerId          — creators this viewer follows
    20| *   GET  /stories                     — active (non-expired) stories
    21| *   POST /stories                     — promote a video to a 24h story
    22| *   GET  /live                        — live sessions (?include_ended=1)
    23| *   POST /live/start                  — { host_id, title, playback_url? } → session with ingest_url + playback_url
    24| *   GET  /live/:sessionId/status      — session lifecycle (created|live|ended|failed)
    25| *   POST /live/:sessionId/ingest      — binary MPEG-TS segment body (?duration=seconds) → live HLS playlist
    26| *   POST /live/:sessionId/stop        — host stop; finalizes playlist with ENDLIST
    27| *   POST /live/:sessionId/moderate    — owner force-end { moderator_id, reason? }
    28| *   GET  /creator/:creatorId/dashboard — creator analytics rollup
    29| *   GET  /moderation/queue            — open reports + decisions
    30| *   POST /moderation/:videoId         — { action: approve|reject|flag, reason?, moderator_id? }
    31| */
